@AntoineCribel, @HenryDarch, the evaluation now requires an additional, critical stage of cross-validation ([https://github.com/DeepLabCut/DeepLabCut/blob/master/docs/UseOverviewGuide.md#evaluate-the-trained-network](https://github.com/DeepLabCut/DeepLabCut/blob/master/docs/UseOverviewGuide.md#evaluate-the-trained-network). Something like
`deeplabcut.evaluate_multianimal_crossvalidate(config_path, Shuffles=[1], edgewisecondition=True, leastbpts=1, init_points=20, n_iter=50)` is a great start.
It is only after the best inference parameters are found that you will get the results in the terminal + the .csv file (which will also contains extra metrics such as PCK or the number of misses) ðŸ˜ƒ
